definition.value: Concentration of tetrahydrobiopterin in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) above the upper limit of normal.
The concentration of 5-hydroxyindoleacetic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.
Presence of at least 10% eosinophils in the total cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) leukocyte count.

label.value: Reduced C27 3beta-HSD activity in cultured fibroblasts
Reduced procollagen-lysine,2-oxoglutarate 5-dioxygenase 1 activity in cultured fibroblasts

definition.value: Concentration or activity of fumarylacetoacetate hydrolase (FAH; EC 3.7.1.2) below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.

label.value: Reduced tissue glycine cleavage enzyme activity
Diminished alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase activity in cultured fibroblasts

definition.value: Concentration or activity of the alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase complex as measured in cultured fibroblasts is below the limits of normal. This enzyme is a multienzyme complex consisting of 3 protein subunits, oxoglutarate dehydrogenase, also known as alpha-ketoglutarate dehydrogenase or E1k (EC 1.2.4.2.), dihydrolipoyl succinyltransferase (DLST, or E2k; 126063), and dihydrolipoyl dehydrogenase (DLD, or E3; 238331). The complex catalyzes a key reaction in the Krebs tricarboxylic acid cycle.
Concentration or activity of phosphorylase kinase below the lower limit of normal. This enzyme can be measured in multiple tissues including leukocytes and cultured fibroblasts.
Growth of mycobacteria in a culture derived from cerebrospinal fluid (CSF).

label.value: Positive respiratory tract nucleic acid pathogen test

definition.value: Positive (abnormal) result of a sputum or pharyngeal sample test such as polymerase chain reaction that is targeted against a nucleic acid sequence specific for a pathogen.

label.value: Positive respiratory tract SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus nucleic acid test

definition.value: Detection of SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus nucleic acid in the sputum or pharyngeal sample by a method such as polymerase chain reaction.
Cryptosporidium antigen present in stool. Tests include direct fluorescent-antibody (DFA), which detects intact organisms, and enzyme immunoassays (EIAs), which detect soluble stool antigens.
Abnormal enlargement (swelling) that is restricted to a specific part of a limb.
Any deviation from the normal height of the sclera, the white part of the eye that forms the tough, fibrous outer layer of the exterior of the eyeball.
A type of conjunctivitis that is not characterized by appreciable exudate, i.e., fluid, cells, or other substances that have escaped from blood vessels and have been deposited around the eyelids.

label.value: Vascular compression of the eighth cranial nerve

definition.value: An abnormal enlargement or swelling localized in the heart. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

Abnormal increase in size of the superior olive, also known as the superior olivary complex. The superior olive is a collection of brainstem nuclei that is located in pons, functions in multiple aspects of hearing and is an important component of the ascending and descending auditory pathways of the auditory system.

Abnormal enhancement of CT or MIR contrast medium in the basilar meninges, that is, those located in the basal cisterns or spaces at the base of the brain, due to increased permeability of blood vessels in these areas.
Persistent and substantial increase in diameter diameter and length of the colon.
A fluid-filled sac or cavity that develops due to fluid accumulation within the thyroid tissue.

label.value: Diminished tissue very long-chain acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
Diminished tissue glycogen branching enzyme activity

definition.value: An accessory phalanx of the fourth (ring) finger that is arranged linearly with the other phalanges. Hyperphalangy results from an accessory ossification center at the metacarpophalangeal joint.
Developmental delay of ossification of the distal epiphysis of the femur.
